'''fwupd''' is [[Article description::a automatic, safe and reliable way for updating firmware on Linux.]] Vendors can upload firmware images on the [https://fwupd.org/lvfs/devicelist vendor firmware service], which are then distributed to devices all over the world.

== Installation ==

